title: CID3586
extract_protocol_ch1: Single-cell sequencing was performed using the Chromium Single-Cell v2 3’ and 5’ Chemistry Library, Gel Bead, Multiplex and Chip Kits (10X Genomics) according to the manufacturer's protocol. A total of 5,000 to 7,000 cells were targeted per well.
description: ***Raw Data Disclaimer: Raw human data files are deposited to the EGA (EGAS00001005173) to adhere to ethics.***
data_processing: Raw bcl files were demultiplexed and mapped to the reference genome GRCh38 using the Cell Ranger Single Cell v2.0 software (10X Genomics). The EmptyDrops method from the DropletUtils package (v1.2.2) was applied for cell filtering with additional cutoffs for cells with a gene and unique molecular identifier (UMIs) count greater than 200 and 250, respectively, and a mitochondrial percentage less than 20%.
